Scripted button. Increments a number in a specified field between specified maximum and minimum values.

Set the cTargetField of the button to the short name of the field on which it is to act.

The following custom properties should be set on the field on which the button is to act:

cMinValue - minimum value the field should be set to.
cMaxValue - maximum value the field should be set to.

Note: A closeField message is sent to the field after the button is used. To avoid a script error, handle the closeField message in the field or comment the relevant line in the button.

The button references 3 images. The ids for these images are stored in the following custom properties set on the button:

cIcon
cUpIcon
cDownIcon

The icon of the button can be set to the cDisabledIcon of the button for a disabled appearance.

Note that this control requires the "Revolution Icons" image library to be tranferred to your stack using Distribution Builder when you are preparing your stack for distribution.